JOHANNESBURG - Standard and Poor's is expected to make an announcement on South Africa's credit rating on Friday.On Thursday, Fitch said the country's foreign and local currency issuer ratings are stable.S&P and Fitch both downgraded the country to junk status after President Jacob Zuma's cabinet reshuffle in March.READ: Standard and Poor's to decide on SA credit ratingMoody's is also expected to announce its rating soon.Treasury is of course hoping for a positive outcome.The rand strengthened slightly against the dollar on Thursday when Fitch issued the stable outlook on long-term local and foreign currency.eNCA